  "description": "MBOX-357 (P1 T5) \u2014 IMAP/SMTP egress, the per-transport sibling of MailBOX-Send (DR-56 Option A). The dashboard's send trigger (lib/n8n.ts) routes here via N8N_IMAP_WEBHOOK_URL when the draft's account is an IMAP provider, leaving MailBOX-Send (the live Gmail critical path) byte-untouched. Same { draft_id } contract + send_attempt_at CAS idempotency lock (migration 025) as the Gmail path; the only differences are the SMTP Send Email node instead of Gmail Reply, and writing the provider-neutral drafts.provider_message_id (not sent_gmail_message_id). The 'Already Sent?' guard keys on provider_message_id. ON IMPORT: (1) create + link an SMTP credential ('MailBox SMTP') for the operator's outbound server (DR-58: app-password / basic-auth v1, domain-aligned per NC-37 \u2014 no relay); (2) re-point the Postgres credential id if it differs. EXPRESSION CONVENTION (MBOX-344): Send Email + Mark Sent IMAP read $('Load Draft IMAP').item.json.* \u2014 NEVER bare $json \u2014 because Acquire Send Lock (RETURNING id) sits between and would blank a bare $json read. S-MP-2 RESIDUAL: emailSend sets To/Subject(Re:)/body + replyTo; true RFC In-Reply-To/References threading headers are tuned/verified on the M1 test rig (kill-criterion: ship flat + flag degraded mode).",
